{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Do2DxKM8ttjyjXYSPqSbSm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation History — 305-peek-operations-admin\n2\t\n3\tIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n4\tattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n5\tof every iteration to understand prior context.\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-25\n10\t\n11\t- Added `jose@6.2.2` to `peek/package.json` as a runtime dep.\n12\t- Rewrote `peek/src/server/cloudflare-access.ts` on top of `jose`:\n13\t  `jwtVerify` with `algorithms: ['RS256']`, `audience`, `issuer`, and\n14\t  `currentDate`, using `createLocalJWKSet` when callers pass an in-memory\n15\t  JWKS (test path) and `createRemoteJWKSet` against\n16\t  `${teamDomain}/cdn-cgi/access/certs` otherwise (cached per issuer).\n17\t- Removed all custom RSA/JWKS/base64url/JSON-claim crypto helpers; mapped\n18\t  jose error subclasses (`JWTExpired`, `JWTClaimValidationFailed` with\n19\t  `claim === \"iss\"`/`\"aud\"`, `JOSEAlgNotAllowed`, `JOSENotSupported`,\n20\t  `JWKSNoMatchingKey`, `JWSSignatureVerificationFailed`,\n21\t  `JWKSTimeout`/`JWKSInvalid`/`JWKInvalid`, `JWTInvalid`/`JWSInvalid`)\n22\t  back onto the existing `CloudflareAccessVerificationReason` union so\n23\t  callers and existing tests are unchanged.\n24\t- Preserved the public surface: `verifyCloudflareAccessJwt`,\n25\t  `getVerifiedCloudflareAccessEmailFromHeaders`, and\n26\t  `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` keep their shapes; `proxy.ts` and\n27\t  `app/layout.tsx` need no edits.\n28\t- Targeted check: `pnpm --dir peek lint`, `pnpm --dir peek typecheck`,\n29\t  and `pnpm --dir peek test` — all green; 21/21 unit tests pass.\n30\t\n31\t## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-25T09:45:06Z — BLOCKED\n32\t- **Blocker**: No file changes detected — agent made no progress.\n33\t- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n34\t\n35\t## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-25\n36\t\n37\t- Expanded `peek/src/server/__tests__/cloudflare-access.test.ts` for the\n38\t  jose-backed verifier: malformed token, expired (`exp` in the past),\n39\t  invalid issuer (signed with `https://other.cloudflareaccess.com`),\n40\t  invalid audience, bad signature (sign with key A, present JWK B with\n41\t  the same `kid`), `alg: \"none\"` rejection, missing email claim\n42\t  (returns `ok: true, email: null`), and case/whitespace normalization\n43\t  (`\"  Admin@Example.COM  \"` → `\"admin@example.com\"`).\n44\t- Lowercased + trimmed in `normalizeEmail` so the verified email\n45\t  identity is canonical for FR-2 role matching.\n46\t- Replaced the implicit `NODE_ENV === \"development\"` bypass in\n47\t  `peek/proxy.ts` with the spec-required explicit `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`\n48\t  bypass: dev-only, validates email shape, sets the\n49\t  `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` so server context still gets a normalized\n50\t  actor identity. Production never honors the bypass; missing CF env in\n51\t  prod still returns 500.\n52\t- Rewrote `peek/src/server/__tests__/cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts`\n53\t  with `vi.stubEnv` (TS forbids assigning to `process.env.NODE_ENV`) and\n54\t  added: prod blocks without JWT (existing), prod 500 on missing CF env,\n55\t  prod ignores `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`, dev honors `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`\n56\t  with case normalization, dev rejects malformed `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`.\n57\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n58\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, +10 new).\n59\t\n60\t## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-25T10:32:41Z — OK\n61\t- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n62\t\n63\t## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-25\n64\t\n65\t- Added `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`:\n66\t  - `PeekRole = \"business\" | \"admin\"`, `PeekRolePolicyEntry = { match, role }`\n67\t    where `match` is either an exact email (`alice@example.com`) or a wildcard\n68\t    domain (`*@example.com`).\n69\t  - `parsePeekRolePolicy(raw)` validates entries: trims/lowercases, drops\n70\t    invalid `role` values, drops missing/non-string `match` values, validates\n71\t    wildcard domain shape, and de-duplicates exact `(match, role)` pairs.\n72\t  - `loadPeekRolePolicyFromEnv()` reads `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` JSON; returns\n73\t    `[]` on missing/malformed input (fail-closed for env-driven config).\n74\t  - `normalizeActorEmail()` and `resolveRoleForEmail()` implement\n75\t    case-insensitive matching and admin precedence: any matching `admin`\n76\t    rule wins (short-circuit), otherwise first matching `business` wins.\n77\t  - `getPeekActorContext()` reads `next/headers` for the trusted\n78\t    `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` (set only by the proxy), normalizes it,\n79\t    resolves the role, and returns `{ email, role }` or `null`. Browser\n80\t    headers are never trusted — the policy is loaded from server env only.\n81\t- Hardened `peek/proxy.ts`: clones `request.headers` and unconditionally\n82\t  `delete()`s `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` at the top of every code path,\n83\t  so a spoofed `x-peek-verified-access-email` header from the browser cannot\n84\t  survive into server context — even on the dev no-config and dev no-bypass\n85\t  branches. The header is only ever (re-)set with the dev-bypass email or a\n86\t  jose-verified Cloudflare Access email.\n87\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n88\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, no regressions; access-policy unit tests land in\n89\t  the next iteration per the checklist split).\n90\t\n91\t## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-25T10:36:33Z — OK\n92\t- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n93\t\n94\t## Iteration 4 — 2026-04-25\n95\t\n96\t- Extended `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts` with the FR-2 centralized\n97\t  route-prefix and action-id authorization helpers:\n98\t  - `PEEK_ROUTE_RULES` table (`/audit` → `admin`); other routes fall back to\n99\t    `PEEK_DEFAULT_ROUTE_ROLES = [\"business\", \"admin\"]` per System Invariant\n100\t    #6 (read-only default for any resolved peek role)."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id"