{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01981J5bVvGbcEfQLo7ApC7V","type":"tool_result","content":"4350\t        rows must reflect a real movement).\n4351\t      - row status is still `scheduled` but `starts_at <= now()` ->\n4352\t        thrown error `starts_at_in_past` -> `execution_failed:\n4353\t        starts_at_in_past`. This closes the \"scheduled\" promotion\n4354\t        race: the worker that flips `scheduled` -> `active` runs out\n4355\t        of band, so admins should not be able to win that race by\n4356\t        hand.\n4357\t      - unknown id -> `execution_failed: unknown_event: <id>`.\n4358\t  - **\"before/after audit\"** — the mutation returns\n4359\t    `[{ field: \"status\", before: \"scheduled\", after: \"cancelled\" }]`\n4360\t    so the runner-emitted `peek.change.applied` payload's `changes`\n4361\t    array pins both ends of the state movement.\n4362\t  - **Authorization** — `dogpile.cancel` is admin-only per the FR-2\n4363\t    `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` rule already declared in\n4364\t    `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts:157`. The runner enforces this\n4365\t    before `execute` is called, so a non-admin actor sees\n4366\t    `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason: \"unauthorized\"` and\n4367\t    no SQL is issued.\n4368\t\n4369\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4370\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4371\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4372\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (81 files, 919/919 — no\n4373\t    regressions; dedicated mutation tests land in the next iteration\n4374\t    \"[test] Dogpile cancellation tests\").\n4375\t\n4376\t- **Next**: `[test] Dogpile cancellation tests: scheduled success,\n4377\t  active/ended denial, unknown event, unauthorized actor, audit\n4378\t  payload.`\n4379\t## Iteration 149 — 2026-04-26T15:47:16Z — OK\n4380\t- **Log**: iteration-149.log\n4381\t\n4382\t\n4383\t\n4384\t## Iteration 150 — 2026-04-26 — Dogpile cancellation tests\n4385\t\n4386\t- **Item**: `[test] Dogpile cancellation tests: scheduled success,\n4387\t  active/ended denial, unknown event, unauthorized actor, audit\n4388\t  payload.`\n4389\t\n4390\t- **Files added** (1):\n4391\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/__tests__/dogpile.test.ts` — 17 unit\n4392\t    tests covering schema, status enum, definition wiring, and the\n4393\t    full runner-orchestrated FR-14 path for `dogpile.cancel`.\n4394\t\n4395\t- **Test groups**:\n4396\t  - `dogpileCancelInputSchema`: valid id, trim, non-numeric reject,\n4397\t    mixed alphanumeric reject, empty-after-trim reject, strict\n4398\t    extra-fields reject (6 tests).\n4399\t  - `DOGPILE_EVENT_STATUSES`: enumerates `scheduled`/`active`/`ended`/\n4400\t    `cancelled` (1 test).\n4401\t  - `dogpileCancelMutation definition`: pins `actionId` and\n4402\t    `resourceType` so audit-row contract regressions break a test\n4403\t    rather than ship silently (1 test).\n4404\t  - `dogpile.cancel via runPeekMutation` (9 tests):\n4405\t    - **Scheduled + future starts_at success** — emits\n4406\t      `peek.change.applied` with `[{ field: \"status\", before:\n4407\t      \"scheduled\", after: \"cancelled\" }]`, transaction begins exactly\n4408\t      once, rolls back never, SELECT precedes UPDATE, UPDATE binds the\n4409\t      `eventId` and includes the `status = 'cancelled'` literal, audit\n4410\t      payload's `requestId` + `actorEmail` + `route` round-trip, and\n4411\t      audit is written on the in-tx Sql so the change + audit row are\n4412\t      atomic.\n4413\t    - **active denial** — `peek.change.rejected` with\n4414\t      `execution_failed: invalid_status: active`, transaction rolls\n4415\t      back, no UPDATE issued, `payload.changes === null`.\n4416\t    - **ended denial** — same shape with `invalid_status: ended`.\n4417\t    - **cancelled (no-op) denial** — same shape with\n4418\t      `invalid_status: cancelled`, asserting that re-cancelling an\n4419\t      already-cancelled row is rejected because FR-14 audit rows must\n4420\t      reflect a real movement.\n4421\t    - **starts_at in past** — scheduled in DB but `starts_at <= now()`\n4422\t      → `execution_failed: starts_at_in_past`. Documents the worker\n4423\t      promotion-from-scheduled race so admins cannot win it from the\n4424\t      admin UI.\n4425\t    - **Unknown event** — empty SELECT result returns\n4426\t      `execution_failed: unknown_event: <id>`; transaction still\n4427\t      begins (and rolls back) so the SELECT-not-found path is covered\n4428\t      end-to-end.\n4429\t    - **Non-admin actor (business)** — runner short-circuits before\n4430\t      `sql.begin`; `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason:\n4431\t      \"unauthorized\"` and zero SQL calls.\n4432\t    - **Null actor role** — same denial path; `rejectionReason:\n4433\t      \"unauthorized\"`.\n4434\t    - **Schema rejection** — non-numeric `eventId=\"abc\"` returns\n4435\t      `invalid_input` with `fieldErrors.eventId`; no transaction\n4436\t      opened; audit row carries `rejectionReason: \"invalid_input\"`\n4437\t      and `payload.changes === null`.\n4438\t\n4439\t- **Test scaffolding parity with `kol-rate.test.ts` /\n4440\t  `fraud-flag.test.ts`**:\n4441\t  - `createAuditWriter()` records `eventType` + `payload` + which\n4442\t    `Sql` was used.\n4443\t  - `createSqlMock()` emulates `sql.begin` and the tagged-template\n4444\t    invocation pattern, returning the `existingRow` for SELECTs\n4445\t    (shaped as `{id, status, startsInFuture}` to match\n4446\t    `dogpile.ts:fetchExistingRow`) and optionally rejecting UPDATEs\n4447\t    via `failOnUpdate` (parallel to fraud-flag's `failOnUpdate`).\n4448\t  - `REGISTRY` is a frozen single-entry registry holding only\n4449\t    `dogpileCancelMutation` so the runner test path doesn't pull in\n4450\t    unrelated production mutations.\n4451\t\n4452\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4453\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4454\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4455\t  - `cd peek &